<br>
My enchanter friend gets the &quot;Your target is immune to the stun portion of this spell&quot; yet good old Jobober keeps on stunning away.<br>
<br>
I've seen my 61 air pet stun level 64 mobs and stuff.   If the wizard pet could do the same, there's a remote possibility that it might be useful in some situations.   However, it's questionable; sure the pet might stun reducing the amount of heals, but the fight could last a bit longer (in an exp group notably) because the pet isn't pumping out 60-70dps like the air pet.   The air pet does stun quite a bit.<br>
<br>
Plus.  If it's a wizard pet, since when is a wizards' primary function stunning?   Like most people, I'd like to have the thing throw some nice cold-based nukes at a mob, since we get none ourselves.  A level 20 100dmg nuke doesn't cut it. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cbreaker1212>CBreaker1212</A> at: 1/17/03 9:02:50 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fabbz>Fabbz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#333333>(1/21/03 3:42:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=161.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: stuns...</span><hr size=1> not sure where i saw this test, but i thought back when pop first came out (need 60-con pet to make resists reasonably low) someone did a test and found out that since pets were NPC's they just ignore the max level on stuns.  racial unstunnable tags will still block all stuns.<br>
<br>
the difference between the chanter there and your pet is pet casts a combo damage/stun, even if it's stun-immune the damage hits and you see a message.  having an immune target only reports to the caster, which would be the pet, so that message just disappears. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=missei>missei</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#333333>(2/6/03 4:25:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=161.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   air</span><hr size=1> In answer to the question about BoT gaters yes. I group in BoT a lot and the best group I was in by far had 3 65 mages in it. Not only do the 3 air pets keep mobs perma stunned and interupt gate and all other casts but our DPS killed mobs like they were orc pawns.  Even the named were all really easy that way, not that they are hard with only one mage, but they get killed a lot faster and everyone with more mana with more mages. <br>
<br>
I have the epic pet, 61, 62, and 65 pets and all I ever use in xp groups is the 61 pet. The 62 pet actually has better dps but without the stuns it doesnt matter in BoT and HoH and even in PoV. The amount these pets stun makes the healers have to heal less and the mobs die faster, its a lot easier to chain pull. While soloing and duoing where pet would be tanking the air pet is still the best in all tier 1 and tier 2 pop zones. The stuns are invaluable. Even though the earth has a ton of HP the healer is constantly healing it. I tested it out same mobs same healer and me with all 4 of those pets tanking and the air conserved the healers mana more than any others, all because the stuns land constantly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mevlar1>Mevlar1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#333333>(2/16/03 8:36:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=161.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Fire pets</span><hr size=1> If the damn thing wouldn't root maybe I could use it in group situations as a stunner,  I pull up a fire pet, have it root the mob, the mob turns and eats the rogue. =/<br>
